---
description: TypeScript and coding style standards
globs: ["src/**/*.{ts,tsx}"]
alwaysApply: true
---

- Use strict TypeScript.
- Do not use `any` unless explicitly justified and documented inline.
- Prefer named types/interfaces for non-trivial objects.
- Keep functions small, deterministic, and side-effect aware.
- Use descriptive names (`slotMinutes`, `eventStartMs`, `visibleRangeStart`).
- Avoid magic numbers: extract constants.
- Fail fast on invalid input and return explicit errors.
